window.__SCRIBE_DOC_SEARCH__ = [{"page":"index.html","title":"Overview","section":"Get oriented","excerpt":"A practical map of the writing workspace, its current capabilities, and the fastest route into the codebase.","content":"ScribeAI developer documentation This directory describes the application as it works now. It is intended to get a developer from a fresh checkout to making safe changes without first reverse-engineering the UI, editor, and suggestion state machine. What this application is ScribeAI is an Electron writing workspace with a React renderer. The current implementation combines: - a BlockNote rich-text editor; - persistent live and development-injected writing-partner feeds; - an inbox for reading, dismissing, pinning, and previewing suggestions; - desktop workspace cards for keeping references over the editor; - responsive navigation and writing-partner panels; - SQLite document, Markdown mirror, source, and suggestion persistence; - a durable Pi coding-agent session with writer-controlled autonomous work and launch-scoped activity diagnostics. Electron owns SQLite and Pi in utility processes, imports UTF-8 Markdown sources, and restores the workspace and Pi session after restart. Development uses the same runtime with Vite renderer HMR and a dedicated mock-suggestion window. Fastest route into the codebase 1. Follow Getting started to run the app, configure the Pi agent under Electron"},{"page":"index.html#what-this-application-is","title":"What this application is","section":"Overview","excerpt":"ScribeAI is an Electron writing workspace with a React renderer. The current implementation combines: - a BlockNote rich-text editor; - persistent live and development-injected writing-partner feeds; - an inbox for readi","content":"What this application is ScribeAI is an Electron writing workspace with a React renderer. The current implementation combines: - a BlockNote rich-text editor; - persistent live and development-injected writing-partner feeds; - an inbox for reading, dismissing, pinning, and previewing suggestions;"},{"page":"index.html#fastest-route-into-the-codebase","title":"Fastest route into the codebase","section":"Overview","excerpt":"1. Follow Getting started to run the app, configure the Pi agent under Electron userData, import Markdown sources, and run the checks. 2. Read Architecture for state ownership and module boundaries. 3. Read Editor and su","content":"Fastest route into the codebase 1. Follow Getting started to run the app, configure the Pi agent under Electron userData, import Markdown sources, and run the checks. 2. Read Architecture for state ownership and module boundaries. 3. Read Editor and suggestion system before changing feed, preview, pin, or inbox behavior."},{"page":"index.html#current-user-visible-behavior","title":"Current user-visible behavior","section":"Overview","excerpt":"","content":"Current user-visible behavior "},{"page":"index.html#repository-map","title":"Repository map","section":"Overview","excerpt":". ├── docs/ Developer documentation ├── desktop/ Electron main, preload, storage, Pi, and build entries ├── src/ │ ├── App.tsx Layout composition root │ ├── main.tsx React renderer entry point │ ├── index.css Tailwind th","content":"Repository map . ├── docs/ Developer documentation ├── desktop/ Electron main, preload, storage, Pi, and build entries ├── src/ │ ├── App.tsx Layout composition root │ ├── main.tsx React renderer entry point │ ├── index.css Tailwind theme, layout rules, and editor overrides"},{"page":"index.html#terms-used-in-the-code","title":"Terms used in the code","section":"Overview","excerpt":"- Suggestion feed : the subscription interface that emits committed suggestion events. - Inbox entry : a live suggestion tracked by the reducer, including viewed, stale, and withdrawn flags. - Pinned entry : a deep-copie","content":"Terms used in the code - Suggestion feed : the subscription interface that emits committed suggestion events. - Inbox entry : a live suggestion tracked by the reducer, including viewed, stale, and withdrawn flags. - Pinned entry : a deep-copied, stable suggestion snapshot removed from the live inbox queue."},{"page":"index.html#important-implementation-constraints","title":"Important implementation constraints","section":"Overview","excerpt":"- App.tsx is the renderer layout composition root. useWorkspaceController connects the Electron bridge, hydration, autosave, feed, previews, agent runtime, and inbox. - inboxReducer is the source of truth for suggestion ","content":"Important implementation constraints - App.tsx is the renderer layout composition root. useWorkspaceController connects the Electron bridge, hydration, autosave, feed, previews, agent runtime, and inbox. - inboxReducer is the source of truth for suggestion lifecycle rules. UI components dispatch intent; they should not recreate those rules locally."},{"page":"getting-started.html","title":"Getting started","section":"Get oriented","excerpt":"Install, run, inspect, and troubleshoot the project from a clean checkout.","content":"Getting started Prerequisites - Node.js =22.19.0. Pi agent-core sets the effective project minimum. - npm, using the committed package-lock.json. No database daemon is required. Electron creates its SQLite database in the platform application-data directory. An API key or local inference endpoint is only required when enabling the Pi agent. Install and run From the repository root: Vite builds the Electron main, preload, storage, and agent entries, starts its renderer development server, and launches Electron. Renderer changes use HMR; main, storage, or agent changes restart Electron; preload changes reload the renderer. Development intentionally uses Electron's persistent userData directory instead of a throwaway Vite profile. Edits, imported sources, settings, and mock suggestions therefore survive restarts and can affect the same persisted workspace as a built application when both resolve to the same app-data profile. Do not run development and an installed build concurrently against that profile. Use npm ci, rather than npm install, for a clean checkout or CI job so dependency versions remain aligned with the lockfile. To build and launch the persistent desktop application: Th"},{"page":"getting-started.html#prerequisites","title":"Prerequisites","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"- Node.js =22.19.0. Pi agent-core sets the effective project minimum. - npm, using the committed package-lock.json. No database daemon is required. Electron creates its SQLite database in the platform application-data di","content":"Prerequisites - Node.js =22.19.0. Pi agent-core sets the effective project minimum. - npm, using the committed package-lock.json. No database daemon is required. Electron creates its SQLite database in the platform application-data directory. An API key or local inference endpoint is only required when enabling the Pi agent."},{"page":"getting-started.html#install-and-run","title":"Install and run","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"From the repository root: npm ci npm run dev Vite builds the Electron main, preload, storage, and agent entries, starts its renderer development server, and launches Electron. Renderer changes use HMR; main, storage, or ","content":"Install and run From the repository root: npm ci npm run dev Vite builds the Electron main, preload, storage, and agent entries, starts its renderer development server, and launches Electron. Renderer changes use HMR; main, storage, or agent changes restart Electron; preload changes reload the renderer."},{"page":"getting-started.html#local-data-layout","title":"Local data layout","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"means the directory returned by Electron's app.getPath(\"userData\") for the running app. For a packaged ScribeAI build this is normally: The running app owns this tree: / scribe.sqlite3 pi/ settings.json auth.json models.","content":"Local data layout means the directory returned by Electron's app.getPath(\"userData\") for the running app. For a packaged ScribeAI build this is normally: The running app owns this tree: / scribe.sqlite3 pi/ settings.json auth.json models.json projects/default-project/"},{"page":"getting-started.html#what-to-expect-after-startup","title":"What to expect after startup","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Electron opens the persisted writing workspace with the agent stopped. Import sources and edit the draft without model activity, then choose Start Agent in the writing-partner toolbar when ready. Stop Agent immediately c","content":"What to expect after startup Electron opens the persisted writing workspace with the agent stopped. Import sources and edit the draft without model activity, then choose Start Agent in the writing-partner toolbar when ready. Stop Agent immediately cancels active model work and keeps later revisions queued until the next start."},{"page":"getting-started.html#set-up-the-pi-agent","title":"Set up the Pi agent","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Launch the app once before configuring Pi so Electron creates /. Then add Pi's native configuration files under /pi/. settings.json selects the default provider and model: { \"defaultProvider\": \"anthropic\", \"defaultModel\"","content":"Set up the Pi agent Launch the app once before configuring Pi so Electron creates /. Then add Pi's native configuration files under /pi/. settings.json selects the default provider and model: { \"defaultProvider\": \"anthropic\", \"defaultModel\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\""},{"page":"getting-started.html#import-writing-sources","title":"Import writing sources","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Use the Electron app to import sources: 1. Open the sidebar section labelled AI research context . 2. Choose Upload Sources . 3. Select a UTF-8 .md or .markdown file. Electron copies the selected file into /projects/defa","content":"Import writing sources Use the Electron app to import sources: 1. Open the sidebar section labelled AI research context . 2. Choose Upload Sources . 3. Select a UTF-8 .md or .markdown file. Electron copies the selected file into /projects/default-project/sources/, records it in SQLite, adds it to the sidebar, and increments the project revision. A running agent wakes immediately; a stopped agent retains the latest revision for the next start. Name collisions are kept readable, for example notes (2).md."},{"page":"getting-started.html#developer-commands","title":"Developer commands","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"A normal pre-handoff check is: npm run lint npm test npm run build See Testing and quality for the current automated coverage and manual checks. The production build currently completes with Vite's warning that some mini","content":"Developer commands A normal pre-handoff check is: npm run lint npm test npm run build See Testing and quality for the current automated coverage and manual checks. The production build currently completes with Vite's warning that some minified chunks exceed 500 kB. The main application bundle and parts of Mermaid are the principal contributors. This is a warning, not a failed build; treat a new error separately. The performance watch points in the Extension guide describe the relevant boundaries."},{"page":"getting-started.html#runtime-entry-points","title":"Runtime entry points","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"- initial editor content: initialContent; - Electron-only mock suggestion controller: src/dev/mockSuggestions; - autonomous Pi runtime and extension: agent.ts and scribe-extension.ts.","content":"Runtime entry points - initial editor content: initialContent; - Electron-only mock suggestion controller: src/dev/mockSuggestions; - autonomous Pi runtime and extension: agent.ts and scribe-extension.ts."},{"page":"getting-started.html#renderer-preferences","title":"Renderer preferences","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"The app stores two optional values: Invalid or unavailable values are ignored. Double-clicking a resize separator removes its key and restores the CSS default. If browser storage is blocked, resizing still works for the ","content":"Renderer preferences The app stores two optional values: Invalid or unavailable values are ignored. Double-clicking a resize separator removes its key and restores the CSS default. If browser storage is blocked, resizing still works for the current session. These values remain renderer-local in both runtimes. Electron workspace data lives in scribe.sqlite3 under Electron's userData directory."},{"page":"getting-started.html#first-pass-manual-tour","title":"First-pass manual tour","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"At a viewport at least 80rem wide: 1. Inject one suggestion of each kind from Development → Mock suggestions . 2. Open a text suggestion, preview it, edit the purple preview block, then cancel it. 3. Preview again and ac","content":"First-pass manual tour At a viewport at least 80rem wide: 1. Inject one suggestion of each kind from Development → Mock suggestions . 2. Open a text suggestion, preview it, edit the purple preview block, then cancel it. 3. Preview again and accept it; it becomes a normal paragraph and the suggestion disappears."},{"page":"getting-started.html#common-problems","title":"Common problems","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"","content":"Common problems "},{"page":"getting-started.html#vite-refuses-to-start","title":"Vite refuses to start","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Check node --version. Vite 8 does not support early Node 20 releases; use Node 20.19 or newer, or Node 22.12 or newer.","content":"Vite refuses to start Check node --version. Vite 8 does not support early Node 20 releases; use Node 20.19 or newer, or Node 22.12 or newer."},{"page":"getting-started.html#electron-opens-a-blank-window","title":"Electron opens a blank window","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Inspect dist/index.html. Built script, stylesheet, module-preload, and lazy-chunk URLs must be relative to the file, such as ./assets/index-….js. vite.config.ts sets base: \"./\" for this reason. Root-relative /assets/... ","content":"Electron opens a blank window Inspect dist/index.html. Built script, stylesheet, module-preload, and lazy-chunk URLs must be relative to the file, such as ./assets/index-….js. vite.config.ts sets base: \"./\" for this reason. Root-relative /assets/... references resolve from the filesystem root under Electron and fail with ERR FILE NOT FOUND."},{"page":"getting-started.html#electron-starts-but-no-window-appears","title":"Electron starts but no window appears","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Run Electron with logging enabled and inspect Desktop startup failed plus utility-process stderr. Main waits for both storage and agent readiness before creating the window. Keep the ES-module entry free of a top-level a","content":"Electron starts but no window appears Run Electron with logging enabled and inspect Desktop startup failed plus utility-process stderr. Main waits for both storage and agent readiness before creating the window. Keep the ES-module entry free of a top-level await app.whenReady(); startup must be attached with app.whenReady().then(start) so module evaluation can complete."},{"page":"getting-started.html#fonts-look-different","title":"Fonts look different","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"index.html loads Inter and Literata from Google Fonts. If the network request is blocked, the UI falls back to system sans-serif and Georgia-style serif fonts. Functionality is unaffected.","content":"Fonts look different index.html loads Inter and Literata from Google Fonts. If the network request is blocked, the UI falls back to system sans-serif and Georgia-style serif fonts. Functionality is unaffected."},{"page":"getting-started.html#a-mind-map-says-diagram-unavailable","title":"A mind map says “Diagram unavailable”","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Mermaid is loaded lazily only when a mind-map visual renders. Invalid Mermaid source or a failed module render activates the accessible text fallback. Inspect MermaidDiagram.tsx and the mermaidSource on the suggestion.","content":"A mind map says “Diagram unavailable” Mermaid is loaded lazily only when a mind-map visual renders. Invalid Mermaid source or a failed module render activates the accessible text fallback. Inspect MermaidDiagram.tsx and the mermaidSource on the suggestion."},{"page":"getting-started.html#a-workspace-pin-is-missing","title":"A workspace pin is missing","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Workspace cards render only at the desktop xl breakpoint (80rem and above). A card also remains hidden for one animation frame while its initial geometry is calculated. It must first be pinned in the writing partner befo","content":"A workspace pin is missing Workspace cards render only at the desktop xl breakpoint (80rem and above). A card also remains hidden for one animation frame while its initial geometry is calculated. It must first be pinned in the writing partner before “Place on workspace” is available."},{"page":"getting-started.html#suggestion-behavior-seems-duplicated-in-development","title":"Suggestion behavior seems duplicated in development","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Check that a new feed is not being created on every render. useWorkspaceController memoizes it. Also ensure every SuggestionFeed.subscribe implementation fully cleans up when the last subscriber leaves; React StrictMode ","content":"Suggestion behavior seems duplicated in development Check that a new feed is not being created on every render. useWorkspaceController memoizes it. Also ensure every SuggestionFeed.subscribe implementation fully cleans up when the last subscriber leaves; React StrictMode will exercise that path."},{"page":"getting-started.html#a-manually-sent-suggestion-does-not-appear","title":"A manually sent suggestion does not appear","section":"Getting started","excerpt":"Confirm the controller was opened from the Electron Development menu rather than by visiting the Vite URL in a browser. Check the controller error message and main-process logs; development injection is rejected outside ","content":"A manually sent suggestion does not appear Confirm the controller was opened from the Electron Development menu rather than by visiting the Vite URL in a browser. Check the controller error message and main-process logs; development injection is rejected outside the Electron development runtime."},{"page":"architecture.html","title":"Architecture","section":"Get oriented","excerpt":"Understand browser and Electron boundaries, state ownership, data direction, and module responsibilities.","content":"Architecture System boundary The React renderer has one application composition: Electron supplies a required preload bridge, main-process orchestration, a SQLite utility process, and a Pi utility process. Vite serves that renderer inside Electron during development and builds it for file:// loading in production. There is still no routing library. The SuggestionFeed remains transport-neutral, while its only application adapter maps committed Electron events. Desktop queries and commands use the typed DesktopBridge contract. Development injection is a separately gated bridge and enters the same persisted storage/event path. Composition root App.tsx is the layout composition root: 1. useCreateBlockNote creates the editor from writingSchema and seeded content. 2. useWorkspaceController owns hydration, serialized autosave, desktop subscriptions, agent controls, inbox integration, and preview coordination. 3. useWorkspaceLayout and useWorkspaceKeybindings connect controller actions to the responsive layout. 4. App composes the editor, sidebars, dock, drawers, and keyboard surfaces. The workspace controller memoizes the desktop suggestion feed. Recreating it during a render would resubs"},{"page":"architecture.html#system-boundary","title":"System boundary","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"The React renderer has one application composition: Electron supplies a required preload bridge, main-process orchestration, a SQLite utility process, and a Pi utility process. Vite serves that renderer inside Electron d","content":"System boundary The React renderer has one application composition: Electron supplies a required preload bridge, main-process orchestration, a SQLite utility process, and a Pi utility process. Vite serves that renderer inside Electron during development and builds it for file:// loading in production. There is still no routing library."},{"page":"architecture.html#composition-root","title":"Composition root","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"App.tsx is the layout composition root: 1. useCreateBlockNote creates the editor from writingSchema and seeded content. 2. useWorkspaceController owns hydration, serialized autosave, desktop subscriptions, agent controls","content":"Composition root App.tsx is the layout composition root: 1. useCreateBlockNote creates the editor from writingSchema and seeded content. 2. useWorkspaceController owns hydration, serialized autosave, desktop subscriptions, agent controls, inbox integration, and preview coordination."},{"page":"architecture.html#state-ownership","title":"State ownership","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"There is intentionally one owner for each lifecycle. Components such as SuggestionDock, WorkspacePins, and DocumentHeader receive values and callbacks; they do not own duplicate application state.","content":"State ownership There is intentionally one owner for each lifecycle. Components such as SuggestionDock, WorkspacePins, and DocumentHeader receive values and callbacks; they do not own duplicate application state."},{"page":"architecture.html#module-boundaries","title":"Module boundaries","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"","content":"Module boundaries "},{"page":"architecture.html#src-editor","title":"src/editor","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- schema.tsx extends BlockNote with the suggestionPreview block and implements accept/cancel behavior. - previewEvents.ts is a small in-process event bridge from the custom block renderer back to App. The editor layer kn","content":"src/editor - schema.tsx extends BlockNote with the suggestionPreview block and implements accept/cancel behavior. - previewEvents.ts is a small in-process event bridge from the custom block renderer back to App. The editor layer knows suggestion IDs, but it does not import or mutate inbox state."},{"page":"architecture.html#src-keybindings-and-src-workspace","title":"src/keybindings and src/workspace","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- commands.ts defines stable semantic command IDs independently of keys and handlers. - defaultKeymap.ts contains the fixed Ctrl+; keymap; sequenceMatcher.ts resolves partial and complete sequences without React or DOM d","content":"src/keybindings and src/workspace - commands.ts defines stable semantic command IDs independently of keys and handlers. - defaultKeymap.ts contains the fixed Ctrl+; keymap; sequenceMatcher.ts resolves partial and complete sequences without React or DOM dependencies. - useKeybindingController.ts owns global keyboard capture and timing. useWorkspaceKeybindings.ts is the only adapter allowed to coordinate editor, layout, and suggestion actions."},{"page":"architecture.html#src-suggestions","title":"src/suggestions","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- types.ts defines suggestion data and the feed interface. - state.ts defines the persisted projection, empty state, 30-entry limit, and shared eviction policy used by renderer and storage. - validation.ts validates sugg","content":"src/suggestions - types.ts defines suggestion data and the feed interface. - state.ts defines the persisted projection, empty state, 30-entry limit, and shared eviction policy used by renderer and storage. - validation.ts validates suggestion payloads at runtime before development IPC reaches storage."},{"page":"architecture.html#src-dev-mocksuggestions","title":"src/dev/mockSuggestions","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"This temporary directory owns the Electron-only controller view and payload builder. Main and preload expose its injection bridge only during Vite development; storage persists accepted mock suggestions exactly like agen","content":"src/dev/mockSuggestions This temporary directory owns the Electron-only controller view and payload builder. Main and preload expose its injection bridge only during Vite development; storage persists accepted mock suggestions exactly like agent-created suggestions."},{"page":"architecture.html#desktop-and-src-desktop","title":"desktop and src/desktop","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- desktop/main.ts owns Electron lifecycle, renderer IPC, utility processes, revision forwarding, and the activity ring. - desktop/storage.ts owns schema creation, SQLite queries, managed Markdown files, and committed eve","content":"desktop and src/desktop - desktop/main.ts owns Electron lifecycle, renderer IPC, utility processes, revision forwarding, and the activity ring. - desktop/storage.ts owns schema creation, SQLite queries, managed Markdown files, and committed events. - desktop/agent.ts creates the durable Pi coding-agent session and drives user-enabled autonomous cycles. Revisions continue to coalesce while the agent is stopped."},{"page":"architecture.html#src-components","title":"src/components","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- EditorWorkspace.tsx joins the document header and editor surface. - DocumentEditor.tsx renders BlockNote and calculates initial workspace-card placement. - SuggestionDock.tsx composes focused activity, detail, and queu","content":"src/components - EditorWorkspace.tsx joins the document header and editor surface. - DocumentEditor.tsx renders BlockNote and calculates initial workspace-card placement. - SuggestionDock.tsx composes focused activity, detail, and queue views. - WorkspacePins.tsx renders desktop cards and handles bounded pointer/keyboard geometry."},{"page":"architecture.html#renderer-bootstrap-sequence","title":"Renderer bootstrap sequence","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"The renderer refuses to construct App without the Electron bridge. The complete process startup is documented separately in Desktop persistence and Pi runtime. sequenceDiagram participant Main as main.tsx participant App","content":"Renderer bootstrap sequence The renderer refuses to construct App without the Electron bridge. The complete process startup is documented separately in Desktop persistence and Pi runtime. sequenceDiagram participant Main as main.tsx participant App participant Controller as useWorkspaceController"},{"page":"architecture.html#data-direction-and-dependency-rules","title":"Data direction and dependency rules","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"The intended dependency direction is: types/contracts ↑ editor utilities suggestion implementations ↑ ↑ components ← props/callbacks → workspace controller / App composition Practical rules: - Domain contracts belong in ","content":"Data direction and dependency rules The intended dependency direction is: types/contracts ↑ editor utilities suggestion implementations ↑ ↑ components ← props/callbacks → workspace controller / App composition Practical rules: - Domain contracts belong in suggestions/types.ts, not in UI components."},{"page":"architecture.html#styling-architecture","title":"Styling architecture","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"Tailwind CSS 4 is loaded through the Vite plugin and @import \"tailwindcss\" in index.css. Most component styling is inline utility classes. The global stylesheet is reserved for: - theme tokens and brand colors; - base fo","content":"Styling architecture Tailwind CSS 4 is loaded through the Vite plugin and @import \"tailwindcss\" in index.css. Most component styling is inline utility classes. The global stylesheet is reserved for: - theme tokens and brand colors; - base focus and typography rules;"},{"page":"architecture.html#build-and-runtime-assumptions","title":"Build and runtime assumptions","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"- TypeScript is strict and emits no files during type-checking. - Vite targets a browser application; there is no server-side rendering guard around browser globals. - Vite's base is ./ because the production renderer is","content":"Build and runtime assumptions - TypeScript is strict and emits no files during type-checking. - Vite targets a browser application; there is no server-side rendering guard around browser globals. - Vite's base is ./ because the production renderer is loaded from file://; changing it back to / breaks all built renderer assets in Electron."},{"page":"architecture.html#architectural-invariants","title":"Architectural invariants","section":"Architecture","excerpt":"Changes should preserve these unless the design is deliberately revised and documented: 1. Only one editable suggestion preview can exist at a time. 2. Preview content is user-owned once inserted; feed updates never over","content":"Architectural invariants Changes should preserve these unless the design is deliberately revised and documented: 1. Only one editable suggestion preview can exist at a time. 2. Preview content is user-owned once inserted; feed updates never overwrite it. 3. Pinned suggestions are frozen snapshots and ignore later feed updates or retractions."},{"page":"architecture-review.html","title":"Architecture review","section":"Get oriented","excerpt":"Review the current architecture, its risks, and a phased path for changing it safely.","content":"Architecture Review This review describes the application as it exists on 2 July 2026 and recommends a path for changing it safely. It is written for the whole team. No knowledge of Electron, React, databases, or artificial-intelligence agent systems is assumed. The assessment was made from the implementation and its tests, independently of the existing architecture guide. Links point to supporting code, but the explanation here is intended to stand on its own. Statements labelled Observed describe current code or validation results. Statements labelled Risk are reasoned consequences that may occur as the product grows. Statements labelled Recommendation propose future work; they do not describe existing behavior. 1. Architecture Present Today What starts, and how the pieces communicate Electron is a framework for shipping a web-style user interface as a desktop application. The Electron host is the complete desktop program. Within it, the application deliberately runs several operating-system processes rather than putting all work in one place: - The main process starts the application, creates windows, opens native file dialogs, and coordinates the other processes. There is one m"},{"page":"architecture-review.html#1-architecture-present-today","title":"1. Architecture Present Today","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"","content":"1. Architecture Present Today "},{"page":"architecture-review.html#what-starts-and-how-the-pieces-communicate","title":"What starts, and how the pieces communicate","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"Electron is a framework for shipping a web-style user interface as a desktop application. The Electron host is the complete desktop program. Within it, the application deliberately runs several operating-system processes","content":"What starts, and how the pieces communicate Electron is a framework for shipping a web-style user interface as a desktop application. The Electron host is the complete desktop program. Within it, the application deliberately runs several operating-system processes rather than putting all work in one place:"},{"page":"architecture-review.html#responsibility-and-state-ownership","title":"Responsibility and state ownership","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"Before naming architectural patterns, the practical ownership is: The renderer uses a React reducer , a function that calculates the next state from the previous state and an action, for suggestion behavior. This makes s","content":"Responsibility and state ownership Before naming architectural patterns, the practical ownership is: The renderer uses a React reducer , a function that calculates the next state from the previous state and an action, for suggestion behavior. This makes selection, dismissal, pinning, workspace placement, previews, and incoming agent events a single explicit state machine : a set of allowed states and transitions. The reducer is pure, meaning it does not perform file, network, or process work while calculating a result. The implementation is in src/suggestions/inbox.ts, and the durable subset of that state is defined in src/suggestions/state.ts."},{"page":"architecture-review.html#interface-composition-and-editing","title":"Interface composition and editing","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"React is the interface library. Its composition root is the place where the major interface parts are created and connected. src/main.tsx obtains the desktop bridge and mounts src/App.tsx. App creates the BlockNote edito","content":"Interface composition and editing React is the interface library. Its composition root is the place where the major interface parts are created and connected. src/main.tsx obtains the desktop bridge and mounts src/App.tsx. App creates the BlockNote editor, workspace layout controller, workspace behavior controller, keyboard controller, navigation, editor, suggestion dock, drawers, and help interface."},{"page":"architecture-review.html#requests-commands-events-and-process-boundaries","title":"Requests, commands, events, and process boundaries","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"A command asks a part of the system to do something, such as “save this document” or “start the agent.” An event reports something that has already happened, such as “the document was saved.” Commands can fail and normal","content":"Requests, commands, events, and process boundaries A command asks a part of the system to do something, such as “save this document” or “start the agent.” An event reports something that has already happened, such as “the document was saved.” Commands can fail and normally have one result. Events may have multiple listeners and should not be treated as requests."},{"page":"architecture-review.html#persistence-hydration-and-autosave","title":"Persistence, hydration, and autosave","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"SQLite is an embedded relational database stored in one local file. It holds one project, one document's BlockNote blocks and Markdown, imported-source metadata, suggestion state, and an event outbox. The database uses w","content":"Persistence, hydration, and autosave SQLite is an embedded relational database stored in one local file. It holds one project, one document's BlockNote blocks and Markdown, imported-source metadata, suggestion state, and an event outbox. The database uses write-ahead logging , which records changes in a companion log before merging them into the main file, and waits for full disk synchronization. Both settings are intended to improve durability. The schema and all storage operations currently share desktop/storage.ts."},{"page":"architecture-review.html#build-validation-and-test-boundaries","title":"Build, validation, and test boundaries","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"The production build has three boundaries. TypeScript checks renderer and desktop code under separate configurations. Vite bundles the React renderer. The Electron plugin builds separate main, storage, agent, and preload","content":"Build, validation, and test boundaries The production build has three boundaries. TypeScript checks renderer and desktop code under separate configurations. Vite bundles the React renderer. The Electron plugin builds separate main, storage, agent, and preload outputs. External package dependencies for Electron processes are left unbundled. Configuration is in package.json, vite.config.ts, tsconfig.app.json, and tsconfig.desktop.json."},{"page":"architecture-review.html#current-strengths-and-constraints","title":"Current strengths and constraints","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"Observed strengths are: - Process isolation. Storage and agent work do not execute in the renderer, and secure window preferences limit renderer privileges (desktop/main.ts). - Explicit bridge contracts. Renderer capabil","content":"Current strengths and constraints Observed strengths are: - Process isolation. Storage and agent work do not execute in the renderer, and secure window preferences limit renderer privileges (desktop/main.ts). - Explicit bridge contracts. Renderer capabilities are named and limited, and subscriptions can be removed (desktop/preload.ts, src/shared/desktop.ts)."},{"page":"architecture-review.html#2-shortcomings-and-recommended-changes","title":"2. Shortcomings and Recommended Changes","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"The findings below separate present behavior from future risk. Effort uses small , medium , or large as relative engineering size. Implementation risk estimates the chance of regressions while making the change. Expected","content":"2. Shortcomings and Recommended Changes The findings below separate present behavior from future risk. Effort uses small , medium , or large as relative engineering size. Implementation risk estimates the chance of regressions while making the change. Expected benefit describes the result if the change succeeds."},{"page":"architecture-review.html#immediate-lower-risk-improvements","title":"Immediate, lower-risk improvements","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"Sequence suggestion saves and make failures visible 1. What currently happens — observed. Every persisted reducer change starts saveSuggestionState without awaiting or queueing prior calls. A rejection is written only to","content":"Immediate, lower-risk improvements Sequence suggestion saves and make failures visible 1. What currently happens — observed. Every persisted reducer change starts saveSuggestionState without awaiting or queueing prior calls. A rejection is written only to the developer console. Unlike document saves, suggestion saves have no expected revision, acknowledgement held in interface state, retry, or visible error (src/workspace/useWorkspaceController.ts)."},{"page":"architecture-review.html#medium-architectural-corrections","title":"Medium architectural corrections","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"Make storage the single authoritative writer for suggestion state 1. What currently happens — observed. Agent commands modify SQLite first and emit events. Renderer actions modify the reducer first and later replace the ","content":"Medium architectural corrections Make storage the single authoritative writer for suggestion state 1. What currently happens — observed. Agent commands modify SQLite first and emit events. Renderer actions modify the reducer first and later replace the whole SQLite projection. Both paths can write the same suggestion state row (desktop/storage.ts, src/suggestions/inbox.ts)."},{"page":"architecture-review.html#larger-strategic-changes","title":"Larger strategic changes","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"Introduce real project and document identities and scoped lifecycles 1. What currently happens — observed. One hard-coded project and one hard-coded document are bootstrapped and queried. The renderer keeps one document ","content":"Larger strategic changes Introduce real project and document identities and scoped lifecycles 1. What currently happens — observed. One hard-coded project and one hard-coded document are bootstrapped and queried. The renderer keeps one document identifier in a ref. Navigation is static and has no route or selection model."},{"page":"architecture-review.html#phased-roadmap","title":"Phased roadmap","section":"Architecture review","excerpt":"The sequence should prioritize correctness and data safety before expanding the product surface: 1. Phase 1 — protect current data and expose failure. Queue and acknowledge suggestion saves, show save failures, add bundl","content":"Phased roadmap The sequence should prioritize correctness and data safety before expanding the product surface: 1. Phase 1 — protect current data and expose failure. Queue and acknowledge suggestion saves, show save failures, add bundle tracking, and add full-application fake-bridge plus process-contract tests. Replace destructive database resets before the next schema change. These steps reduce present risk without changing product scope."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html","title":"Desktop & Pi","section":"Build internals","excerpt":"Trace Electron processes, SQLite persistence, source import, events, and background Pi observations.","content":"Desktop persistence and Pi runtime Process topology The packaged application has four cooperating runtimes: React owns BlockNote and presentation state; Electron main owns lifecycle, IPC, the launch-scoped activity ring, and project revision delivery; the storage utility process exclusively owns SQLite and the managed workspace; and the agent utility process owns one durable @earendil-works/pi-coding-agent session. The preload exposes the typed DesktopBridge. The renderer never imports Electron, SQLite, filesystem, or Pi packages. Managed project workspace Electron resolves with app.getPath(\"userData\"); it is outside the repository and under the platform application-data directory. The default project uses: Accepted BlockNote blocks and the lossy Markdown export are saved together in SQLite at /scribe.sqlite3. Storage atomically replaces draft.md before it commits and publishes the new revision. Startup repairs a missing or damaged mirror from SQLite before the agent is woken. Source import accepts only .md and .markdown. The renderer asks Electron main to open a native file picker from the sidebar's Upload Sources action, then storage validates the complete file as UTF-8 and copie"},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#process-topology","title":"Process topology","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"The packaged application has four cooperating runtimes: React owns BlockNote and presentation state; Electron main owns lifecycle, IPC, the launch-scoped activity ring, and project revision delivery; the storage utility ","content":"Process topology The packaged application has four cooperating runtimes: React owns BlockNote and presentation state; Electron main owns lifecycle, IPC, the launch-scoped activity ring, and project revision delivery; the storage utility process exclusively owns SQLite and the managed workspace; and the agent utility process owns one durable @earendil-works/pi-coding-agent session."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#managed-project-workspace","title":"Managed project workspace","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"Electron resolves with app.getPath(\"userData\"); it is outside the repository and under the platform application-data directory. The default project uses: /projects/default-project/ draft.md sources/ .md .pi/sessions/ .js","content":"Managed project workspace Electron resolves with app.getPath(\"userData\"); it is outside the repository and under the platform application-data directory. The default project uses: /projects/default-project/ draft.md sources/ .md .pi/sessions/ .jsonl Accepted BlockNote blocks and the lossy Markdown export are saved together in SQLite at /scribe.sqlite3. Storage atomically replaces draft.md before it commits and publishes the new revision. Startup repairs a missing or damaged mirror from SQLite before the agent is woken."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#pi-configuration-and-session","title":"Pi configuration and session","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"Pi uses native global files under /pi/: - settings.json for default provider/model and Pi settings; - auth.json for Pi credentials; - models.json for custom models/providers. Standard provider environment variables are a","content":"Pi configuration and session Pi uses native global files under /pi/: - settings.json for default provider/model and Pi settings; - auth.json for Pi credentials; - models.json for custom models/providers. Standard provider environment variables are also supported. Invalid settings, auth, or model files—or no usable model/credential pair—leave the runtime offline and expose a diagnostic in the writing-partner panel."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#autonomous-loop","title":"Autonomous loop","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"There is no polling timer. The Pi utility process and durable session initialize at launch, but autonomous work starts disabled. After storage commits a document or source revision, main forwards that durable revision th","content":"Autonomous loop There is no polling timer. The Pi utility process and durable session initialize at launch, but autonomous work starts disabled. After storage commits a document or source revision, main forwards that durable revision through Pi's shared event bus. The extension coalesces updates while Pi is stopped or busy and starts a cycle against the latest revision only after the writer chooses Start Agent ."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#activity-diagnostics","title":"Activity diagnostics","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"Agent lifecycle, message, emitted reasoning, tool, provider, loop, and error events become agent.activity desktop events. Main aggregates streaming message/tool updates by ID, recursively redacts credential and header fi","content":"Activity diagnostics Agent lifecycle, message, emitted reasoning, tool, provider, loop, and error events become agent.activity desktop events. Main aggregates streaming message/tool updates by ID, recursively redacts credential and header fields, caps each serialized payload at 50 KB, and keeps the latest 500 entries in memory."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#startup-and-failure-behaviour","title":"Startup and failure behaviour","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"Storage is started first, creates/repairs the workspace mirror, and reports readiness. Main then initializes the Pi process, waits for its readiness diagnostic, registers renderer IPC, creates the window, and delivers th","content":"Startup and failure behaviour Storage is started first, creates/repairs the workspace mirror, and reports readiness. Main then initializes the Pi process, waits for its readiness diagnostic, registers renderer IPC, creates the window, and delivers the current revision without starting a model cycle. Utility process startup failure is fatal; provider/tool failures put the enabled autonomous loop to sleep in error until a newer project revision arrives or the writer stops and starts it."},{"page":"desktop-runtime.html#build-and-packaging","title":"Build and packaging","section":"Desktop & Pi","excerpt":"npm run build type-checks both TypeScript projects and builds renderer, main, preload, storage, and agent bundles. npm run package produces an unpacked electron-builder application; npm run dist produces platform package","content":"Build and packaging npm run build type-checks both TypeScript projects and builds renderer, main, preload, storage, and agent bundles. npm run package produces an unpacked electron-builder application; npm run dist produces platform packages. Generated dist-electron/ and release/ directories are not source."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html","title":"Editor & suggestions","section":"Build internals","excerpt":"Trace agent context, feed events, inbox transitions, editable previews, and workspace pins end to end.","content":"Editor and suggestion system This is the core interaction model: the Electron feed emits committed events, the inbox reducer turns those events and user actions into state, and text suggestions can temporarily enter the document as editable previews. Domain model The shared contracts are in src/suggestions/types.ts. Suggestion kinds Kind Type Extra data Can preview into document? Visual treatment --- --- --- --- --- snippet TextSuggestion insertText Yes Text detail fact TextSuggestion insertText Yes Text detail term TextSuggestion insertText Yes Text detail outline StructureSuggestion recursive nodes No Nested structure cards layout StructureSuggestion recursive nodes No Nested structure cards mindMap MindMapSuggestion Mermaid source and accessible description No Lazy-rendered Mermaid diagram Every suggestion also carries: - id: identity for updates, retractions, selection, and actions; - dedupeKey: session-level duplicate prevention for additions; - title, summary, and body: progressively more detailed presentation text; - sourceLabels: display-only attribution labels; - createdAt: ordering and queue-eviction input. An update uses id to replace an existing live item. An addition u"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#domain-model","title":"Domain model","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"The shared contracts are in src/suggestions/types.ts.","content":"Domain model The shared contracts are in src/suggestions/types.ts."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#suggestion-kinds","title":"Suggestion kinds","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"Every suggestion also carries: - id: identity for updates, retractions, selection, and actions; - dedupeKey: session-level duplicate prevention for additions; - title, summary, and body: progressively more detailed prese","content":"Suggestion kinds Every suggestion also carries: - id: identity for updates, retractions, selection, and actions; - dedupeKey: session-level duplicate prevention for additions; - title, summary, and body: progressively more detailed presentation text; - sourceLabels: display-only attribution labels;"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#feed-contract","title":"Feed contract","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"SuggestionFeed is subscription-only: interface SuggestionFeed { subscribe(listener: (event: SuggestionEvent) = void): () = void; } The event channel supports: The renderer uses createDesktopSuggestionFeed. It receives on","content":"Feed contract SuggestionFeed is subscription-only: interface SuggestionFeed { subscribe(listener: (event: SuggestionEvent) = void): () = void; } The event channel supports: The renderer uses createDesktopSuggestionFeed. It receives only committed suggestion events from Electron main. Agent status and errors are reported separately through the canonical AgentRuntime. Suggestions are written to the desktop database before an event is forwarded, so reload hydrates the same inbox projection."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#inbox-state-machine","title":"Inbox state machine","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"inboxReducer owns: entries live inbox suggestions pinnedEntries frozen references in the Pins section workspacePins frozen references placed over the editor seenKeys dedupe keys accepted during this page session selected","content":"Inbox state machine inboxReducer owns: entries live inbox suggestions pinnedEntries frozen references in the Pins section workspacePins frozen references placed over the editor seenKeys dedupe keys accepted during this page session selectedId item shown in detail view"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#feed-event-behavior","title":"Feed-event behavior","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"","content":"Feed-event behavior "},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#queue-limit","title":"Queue limit","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"The live queue is limited to 30. Pins and workspace cards do not count. If eviction is necessary: 1. the selected item and active preview are protected; 2. viewed items are evicted before unread items; 3. within that gro","content":"Queue limit The live queue is limited to 30. Pins and workspace cards do not count. If eviction is necessary: 1. the selected item and active preview are protected; 2. viewed items are evicted before unread items; 3. within that group, the oldest createdAt value is evicted first."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#user-action-behavior","title":"User-action behavior","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"- Selecting marks the item viewed and opens detail. - Back clears detail and removes withdrawn entries unless one still owns the active preview. - Dismiss removes an inbox or pinned item and closes its detail view. Dismi","content":"User-action behavior - Selecting marks the item viewed and opens detail. - Back clears detail and removes withdrawn entries unless one still owns the active preview. - Dismiss removes an inbox or pinned item and closes its detail view. Dismiss is disabled while that item has the active preview."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#editable-preview-lifecycle","title":"Editable preview lifecycle","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"Only snippet, fact, and term suggestions expose “Preview in document.” The orchestration is split between App, the custom BlockNote block, and the inbox reducer. sequenceDiagram participant User participant Dock as Sugge","content":"Editable preview lifecycle Only snippet, fact, and term suggestions expose “Preview in document.” The orchestration is split between App, the custom BlockNote block, and the inbox reducer. sequenceDiagram participant User participant Dock as SuggestionDock participant App"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#preview-insertion","title":"Preview insertion","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"App.handlePreview rejects the request when: - another preview is active; - the suggestion is not a text suggestion; - there is no accepted reference block. It finds the most recently selected text block among accepted bl","content":"Preview insertion App.handlePreview rejects the request when: - another preview is active; - the suggestion is not a text suggestion; - there is no accepted reference block. It finds the most recently selected text block among accepted blocks. If that block no longer exists, it falls back to the final accepted top-level block. The preview is inserted immediately after that block with:"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#preview-rendering-and-resolution","title":"Preview rendering and resolution","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"schema.tsx registers suggestionPreview alongside BlockNote's default blocks. Its React renderer owns the buttons: - Accept is disabled if recursive content inspection finds no visible text. - Accept replaces the custom b","content":"Preview rendering and resolution schema.tsx registers suggestionPreview alongside BlockNote's default blocks. Its React renderer owns the buttons: - Accept is disabled if recursive content inspection finds no visible text. - Accept replaces the custom block with a normal paragraph carrying the edited inline content."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#concurrent-feed-changes","title":"Concurrent feed changes","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"The preview is a snapshot. If the feed updates the source suggestion, the detail view reports that the item was refined, but the user's editable block is never rewritten. If the feed retracts it, the detail view reports ","content":"Concurrent feed changes The preview is a snapshot. If the feed updates the source suggestion, the detail view reports that the item was refined, but the user's editable block is never rewritten. If the feed retracts it, the detail view reports withdrawal and the preview remains resolvable. Cancelling a withdrawn preview removes the suggestion; accepting any preview removes it."},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#pins-and-workspace-cards","title":"Pins and workspace cards","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"Pins are a separate lifecycle from previews: stateDiagram-v2 [ ] -- Inbox: suggestion.added Inbox -- Pins: Pin Pins -- Inbox: Unpin Pins -- Workspace: Place on workspace (desktop) Workspace -- Pins: Return to Pins Inbox ","content":"Pins and workspace cards Pins are a separate lifecycle from previews: stateDiagram-v2 [ ] -- Inbox: suggestion.added Inbox -- Pins: Pin Pins -- Inbox: Unpin Pins -- Workspace: Place on workspace (desktop) Workspace -- Pins: Return to Pins Inbox -- [ ]: Dismiss / accepted preview / retraction"},{"page":"editor-and-suggestions.html#mermaid-rendering","title":"Mermaid rendering","section":"Editor & suggestions","excerpt":"Mind maps use MermaidDiagram: - the mermaid package is imported once, lazily; - the singleton is initialized with securityLevel: \"strict\" and startOnLoad: false; - React IDs are sanitized into per-render Mermaid IDs; - t","content":"Mermaid rendering Mind maps use MermaidDiagram: - the mermaid package is imported once, lazily; - the singleton is initialized with securityLevel: \"strict\" and startOnLoad: false; - React IDs are sanitized into per-render Mermaid IDs; - the rendered SVG is injected into a role=\"img\" container with a combined title and accessible description;"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html","title":"UI & accessibility","section":"Build internals","excerpt":"Work confidently with responsive panels, editor layout, keyboard input, focus, and visual conventions.","content":"UI and accessibility Page regions The application has three conceptual regions: 1. project navigation; 2. the document workspace (header and editor); 3. the writing partner. App renders one desktop grid plus two below-desktop drawers. EditorWorkspace keeps the document header and editor together as the center region. Responsive layout The desktop threshold is 80rem (xl in Tailwind's default scale and the explicit media query in index.css). Viewport Navigation Document Writing partner Workspace cards --- --- --- --- --- =96rem Default 280 px Fluid Default 360 px Visible Opening suggestion detail applies a wider default writing-partner width (clamp(30rem, 38vw, 40rem)) in the first desktop range. An inline user-saved width takes precedence. At 96rem and above, the later large-screen default currently wins in the CSS cascade. Desktop panel open state and mobile drawer open state are intentionally separate. Crossing into desktop closes any open drawers. Collapsing a desktop panel does not imply that its mobile drawer is open, and vice versa. Desktop column resizing ColumnResizeHandle renders an accessible vertical separator on each open side column. Limits Column Minimum Absolute maxim"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#page-regions","title":"Page regions","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"The application has three conceptual regions: 1. project navigation; 2. the document workspace (header and editor); 3. the writing partner. App renders one desktop grid plus two below-desktop drawers. EditorWorkspace kee","content":"Page regions The application has three conceptual regions: 1. project navigation; 2. the document workspace (header and editor); 3. the writing partner. App renders one desktop grid plus two below-desktop drawers. EditorWorkspace keeps the document header and editor together as the center region."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#responsive-layout","title":"Responsive layout","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"The desktop threshold is 80rem (xl in Tailwind's default scale and the explicit media query in index.css). Opening suggestion detail applies a wider default writing-partner width (clamp(30rem, 38vw, 40rem)) in the first ","content":"Responsive layout The desktop threshold is 80rem (xl in Tailwind's default scale and the explicit media query in index.css). Opening suggestion detail applies a wider default writing-partner width (clamp(30rem, 38vw, 40rem)) in the first desktop range. An inline user-saved width takes precedence. At 96rem and above, the later large-screen default currently wins in the CSS cascade."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#desktop-column-resizing","title":"Desktop column resizing","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"ColumnResizeHandle renders an accessible vertical separator on each open side column.","content":"Desktop column resizing ColumnResizeHandle renders an accessible vertical separator on each open side column."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#limits","title":"Limits","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"When the viewport changes, saved widths are constrained again. The values are written to localStorage as the user resizes.","content":"Limits When the viewport changes, saved widths are constrained again. The values are written to localStorage as the user resizes."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#input-behavior","title":"Input behavior","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"- Pointer drag resizes in the expected visual direction. - Arrow keys resize by 16 px. - Home moves to the minimum. - End moves to the current dynamic maximum. - Double-click resets to the responsive CSS default and remo","content":"Input behavior - Pointer drag resizes in the expected visual direction. - Arrow keys resize by 16 px. - Home moves to the minimum. - End moves to the current dynamic maximum. - Double-click resets to the responsive CSS default and removes the stored value."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#responsive-drawers","title":"Responsive drawers","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"ResponsiveDrawer provides both side drawers below desktop: - semantic modal dialog with an accessible title; - backdrop click and explicit close button; - Escape-to-close; - initial focus on the close button; - Tab/Shift","content":"Responsive drawers ResponsiveDrawer provides both side drawers below desktop: - semantic modal dialog with an accessible title; - backdrop click and explicit close button; - Escape-to-close; - initial focus on the close button; - Tab/Shift+Tab wrapping inside known focusable elements;"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#header-controls","title":"Header controls","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"DocumentHeader uses separate controls for desktop columns and mobile drawers, each with the correct aria-controls and aria-expanded state. When the writing partner is not visible, its toggle includes the unread count in ","content":"Header controls DocumentHeader uses separate controls for desktop columns and mobile drawers, each with the correct aria-controls and aria-expanded state. When the writing partner is not visible, its toggle includes the unread count in both the visual badge and accessible label. When the desktop partner is already open, the header suppresses its unread badge because the count is visible in the dock."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#keyboard-shortcuts","title":"Keyboard shortcuts","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"Application shortcuts use Ctrl+; as a leader so normal document typing, BlockNote commands, and common operating-system modifier combinations remain available. The leader and each continuation have a two-second timeout. ","content":"Keyboard shortcuts Application shortcuts use Ctrl+; as a leader so normal document typing, BlockNote commands, and common operating-system modifier combinations remain available. The leader and each continuation have a two-second timeout. Invalid continuations cancel the sequence without consuming the typed character."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#editor-surface","title":"Editor surface","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"DocumentEditor is the only vertically scrolling center-region surface. It renders: - a centered BlockNote editor with a maximum content width of 55rem; - an absolute workspace-card layer over the full editor canvas; - ex","content":"Editor surface DocumentEditor is the only vertically scrolling center-region surface. It renders: - a centered BlockNote editor with a maximum content width of 55rem; - an absolute workspace-card layer over the full editor canvas; - extra minimum canvas height when a workspace card extends beyond the document."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#suggestion-dock-interaction","title":"Suggestion dock interaction","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"The writing partner has two tabs, Suggestions and Activity. Its sticky toolbar also contains the lifecycle control, so Start Agent or Stop Agent remains available from either tab and suggestion detail. The Suggestions ta","content":"Suggestion dock interaction The writing partner has two tabs, Suggestions and Activity. Its sticky toolbar also contains the lifecycle control, so Start Agent or Stop Agent remains available from either tab and suggestion detail. The Suggestions tab has two mutually exclusive views:"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#workspace-card-input-and-bounds","title":"Workspace card input and bounds","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"Workspace cards are desktop reference surfaces, not editor content. WorkspacePins supports: - pointer drag through the card header; - pointer resize through the bottom-right handle; - raising a card when it is interacted","content":"Workspace card input and bounds Workspace cards are desktop reference surfaces, not editor content. WorkspacePins supports: - pointer drag through the card header; - pointer resize through the bottom-right handle; - raising a card when it is interacted with; - automatic clamping when canvas dimensions change;"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#focus-and-semantics-checklist","title":"Focus and semantics checklist","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"When changing UI behavior, retain these existing properties: - icon-only buttons have explicit labels and decorative icons use aria-hidden; - panel controls expose the controlled element and expanded state; - drawers are","content":"Focus and semantics checklist When changing UI behavior, retain these existing properties: - icon-only buttons have explicit labels and decorative icons use aria-hidden; - panel controls expose the controlled element and expanded state; - drawers are named modal dialogs and restore focus;"},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#styling-conventions","title":"Styling conventions","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"Use Tailwind utilities in components for local layout and presentation. Add global CSS only when a selector must target third-party/editor markup, define shared tokens, or coordinate the workspace grid. The brand palette","content":"Styling conventions Use Tailwind utilities in components for local layout and presentation. Add global CSS only when a selector must target third-party/editor markup, define shared tokens, or coordinate the workspace grid. The brand palette is declared as brand-50 through brand-900 in index.css. BlockNote has a parallel set of --bn- variables in the same file. When changing a core color, check both systems as well as hard-coded neutral colors in components."},{"page":"ui-and-accessibility.html#static-prototype-surfaces","title":"Static prototype surfaces","section":"UI & accessibility","excerpt":"Do not infer application behavior from every button currently visible. The sidebar navigation, document-management actions, and tabs are static. Source upload is functional: App supplies persisted source data and an Elec","content":"Static prototype surfaces Do not infer application behavior from every button currently visible. The sidebar navigation, document-management actions, and tabs are static. Source upload is functional: App supplies persisted source data and an Electron import callback to Sidebar. When implementing the remaining controls, add an explicit state/data owner and update this documentation; avoid placing navigation or persistence side effects directly inside presentational components."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html","title":"Testing & quality","section":"Ship safely","excerpt":"Know what the automated suite protects, where browser checks are required, and what to run before handoff.","content":"Testing and quality Test stack - Vitest 4 runs the test suite. - jsdom supplies the browser-like environment configured in vite.config.ts. - Testing Library renders React components and queries their accessible output. - @testing-library/user-event drives user-style interactions. - src/test/setup.ts cleans up rendered React trees after every test. Tests are colocated with source files and use .test.ts or .test.tsx. Commands npm run build is also the authoritative type and bundle check. It type-checks the renderer and Electron projects, then runs the integrated Vite build for renderer, main, preload, storage, and agent entries. TypeScript uses strict mode, rejects unused locals and parameters, and disallows fallthrough switch cases. ESLint enforces a cyclomatic complexity ceiling of 15 per function. Orchestration that exceeds it should be split into named lifecycle or action handlers. Current automated coverage The suite currently contains unit and component coverage across renderer, storage, autonomous-loop, activity, and Pi-session boundaries. File What it protects --- --- suggestions/inbox.test.ts Dedupe, 30-item eviction, stale/withdrawn previews, frozen pins, workspace transiti"},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#test-stack","title":"Test stack","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Vitest 4 runs the test suite. - jsdom supplies the browser-like environment configured in vite.config.ts. - Testing Library renders React components and queries their accessible output. - @testing-library/user-event dr","content":"Test stack - Vitest 4 runs the test suite. - jsdom supplies the browser-like environment configured in vite.config.ts. - Testing Library renders React components and queries their accessible output. - @testing-library/user-event drives user-style interactions."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#commands","title":"Commands","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"npm test npm run test:watch npm run lint npm run build npm run build is also the authoritative type and bundle check. It type-checks the renderer and Electron projects, then runs the integrated Vite build for renderer, m","content":"Commands npm test npm run test:watch npm run lint npm run build npm run build is also the authoritative type and bundle check. It type-checks the renderer and Electron projects, then runs the integrated Vite build for renderer, main, preload, storage, and agent entries. TypeScript uses strict mode, rejects unused locals and parameters, and disallows fallthrough switch cases."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#current-automated-coverage","title":"Current automated coverage","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"The suite currently contains unit and component coverage across renderer, storage, autonomous-loop, activity, and Pi-session boundaries.","content":"Current automated coverage The suite currently contains unit and component coverage across renderer, storage, autonomous-loop, activity, and Pi-session boundaries."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#why-reducer-tests-matter-most","title":"Why reducer tests matter most","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"The inbox reducer contains the application's lifecycle invariants and is pure. Any change to dedupe, updates, retractions, selection, previewing, pins, workspace geometry, queue limits, or unread behavior should begin wi","content":"Why reducer tests matter most The inbox reducer contains the application's lifecycle invariants and is pure. Any change to dedupe, updates, retractions, selection, previewing, pins, workspace geometry, queue limits, or unread behavior should begin with a reducer case. Component tests should then verify that the correct intent is exposed to users."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#development-injection-tests","title":"Development injection tests","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"The controller test injects a callback rather than Electron IPC. Storage tests protect durable development suggestion behavior; manually confirm the development-only preload and main-process gates in Electron.","content":"Development injection tests The controller test injects a callback rather than Electron IPC. Storage tests protect durable development suggestion behavior; manually confirm the development-only preload and main-process gates in Electron."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#geometry-tests","title":"Geometry tests","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"jsdom does not perform layout. Workspace tests mock clientWidth and clientHeight, and pointer-capture methods are stubbed where needed. A passing geometry unit test does not replace Electron renderer testing for actual s","content":"Geometry tests jsdom does not perform layout. Workspace tests mock clientWidth and clientHeight, and pointer-capture methods are stubbed where needed. A passing geometry unit test does not replace Electron renderer testing for actual scroll, resizing, and pointer behavior."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#what-is-not-covered-automatically","title":"What is not covered automatically","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"The current suite does not render the full App or BlockNote editor. It therefore does not directly verify: - preview block insertion, editing, accepting, or cancellation; - panel drag resizing and localStorage restoratio","content":"What is not covered automatically The current suite does not render the full App or BlockNote editor. It therefore does not directly verify: - preview block insertion, editing, accepting, or cancellation; - panel drag resizing and localStorage restoration; - breakpoint transitions and drawer/desktop handoff;"},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#manual-regression-checklist","title":"Manual regression checklist","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"","content":"Manual regression checklist "},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#editor","title":"Editor","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- The seeded document renders and remains editable. - Editing document text does not create suggestions. - Block formatting, selection, slash menu, and normal BlockNote editing still work.","content":"Editor - The seeded document renders and remains editable. - Editing document text does not create suggestions. - Block formatting, selection, slash menu, and normal BlockNote editing still work."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#suggestion-lifecycle","title":"Suggestion lifecycle","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- The inbox remains empty until a controller event is sent. - Each of the six controller kinds appears with its entered content and visual treatment. - The workspace exposes no Generate Ideas, steering, or retry controls","content":"Suggestion lifecycle - The inbox remains empty until a controller event is sent. - Each of the six controller kinds appears with its entered content and visual treatment. - The workspace exposes no Generate Ideas, steering, or retry controls. - Selecting marks an item read; Back returns to the correct queue."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#preview-lifecycle","title":"Preview lifecycle","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Only text kinds offer Preview. - The preview appears after the last active accepted block and receives focus. - Only one preview can be active. - The preview is editable; empty content disables Accept. - Cancel removes","content":"Preview lifecycle - Only text kinds offer Preview. - The preview appears after the last active accepted block and receives focus. - Only one preview can be active. - The preview is editable; empty content disables Accept. - Cancel removes the block and keeps a normal source suggestion."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#desktop-layout-80rem","title":"Desktop layout ( =80rem)","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Both side columns can collapse independently. - Pointer and keyboard resizing respect the editor's minimum space. - Reload restores sizes; double-click resets them. - A pinned detail can be placed on the workspace. - C","content":"Desktop layout ( =80rem) - Both side columns can collapse independently. - Pointer and keyboard resizing respect the editor's minimum space. - Reload restores sizes; double-click resets them. - A pinned detail can be placed on the workspace. - Cards move, resize, stack, clamp, scroll internally, and return to Pins."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#below-desktop-80rem","title":"Below desktop (<80rem)","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Navigation and writing partner open as the correct side drawers. - Escape, backdrop, and close button dismiss a drawer. - Focus enters the drawer, wraps, and returns to the trigger. - Workspace placement is unavailable","content":"Below desktop (<80rem) - Navigation and writing partner open as the correct side drawers. - Escape, backdrop, and close button dismiss a drawer. - Focus enters the drawer, wraps, and returns to the trigger. - Workspace placement is unavailable and no workspace card is shown."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#accessibility","title":"Accessibility","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Complete core flows with keyboard only. - Inspect button/dialog/region names with browser accessibility tools. - Confirm visible focus on all interactive elements. - Confirm unread counts and errors are announced as te","content":"Accessibility - Complete core flows with keyboard only. - Inspect button/dialog/region names with browser accessibility tools. - Confirm visible focus on all interactive elements. - Confirm unread counts and errors are announced as text, not color alone. - Force invalid Mermaid source and confirm the description remains available."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#electron-runtime","title":"Electron runtime","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"- Run npm run dev and confirm Electron launches without manually opening the Vite URL. - Change renderer code and confirm HMR; change main/storage/agent code and confirm Electron restarts; change preload and confirm the ","content":"Electron runtime - Run npm run dev and confirm Electron launches without manually opening the Vite URL. - Change renderer code and confirm HMR; change main/storage/agent code and confirm Electron restarts; change preload and confirm the renderer reloads. - Open Development → Mock suggestions twice and confirm one controller window is focused rather than duplicated."},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#adding-tests","title":"Adding tests","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"Match the test boundary to the behavior: - pure state transition: add to inbox.test.ts; - feed adapter lifecycle: test through SuggestionFeed events with fake time or a controlled transport; - component semantics/callbac","content":"Adding tests Match the test boundary to the behavior: - pure state transition: add to inbox.test.ts; - feed adapter lifecycle: test through SuggestionFeed events with fake time or a controlled transport; - component semantics/callback: render the component with explicit props and query by accessible role/name;"},{"page":"testing-and-quality.html#pre-handoff-standard","title":"Pre-handoff standard","section":"Testing & quality","excerpt":"Before handing off a change: 1. run lint; 2. run all unit/component tests; 3. run the production build; 4. manually exercise each changed flow at the relevant breakpoints; 5. update /docs if a contract, invariant, comman","content":"Pre-handoff standard Before handing off a change: 1. run lint; 2. run all unit/component tests; 3. run the production build; 4. manually exercise each changed flow at the relevant breakpoints; 5. update /docs if a contract, invariant, command, breakpoint, persistence rule, or static/functional boundary changed."},{"page":"extension-guide.html","title":"Extension guide","section":"Ship safely","excerpt":"Use the existing seams to add a real agent, persistence, suggestion kinds, editor blocks, and application actions.","content":"Extension guide This guide identifies the existing seams for likely next steps in the Electron runtime. Evolve the writing-partner transport Keep transport details behind the existing SuggestionFeed contract. The Electron adapter receives committed events from the storage and Pi processes; the development controller injects through that same persisted path. A production adapter must define: - how it starts and stops when subscribers come and go; - how server messages map to every SuggestionEvent variant; - stable id and dedupeKey rules; - reconnection and replay semantics; - ordering of suggestion events; - cleanup under React StrictMode. Choose or introduce adapters in useWorkspaceController. Preserve stable construction with useMemo, or move service creation above React if it is intentionally process-wide. Runtime status and errors remain on AgentRuntime; they are not suggestion-feed events. Do not call an HTTP or model SDK directly from SuggestionDock. That would couple view lifecycle to transport lifecycle, make replay/dedupe inconsistent, and bypass reducer tests. Introduce context for a real service The current application does not publish editor or artifact context to the fe"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#evolve-the-writing-partner-transport","title":"Evolve the writing-partner transport","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Keep transport details behind the existing SuggestionFeed contract. The Electron adapter receives committed events from the storage and Pi processes; the development controller injects through that same persisted path. A","content":"Evolve the writing-partner transport Keep transport details behind the existing SuggestionFeed contract. The Electron adapter receives committed events from the storage and Pi processes; the development controller injects through that same persisted path. A production adapter must define:"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#introduce-context-for-a-real-service","title":"Introduce context for a real service","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The current application does not publish editor or artifact context to the feed. Before introducing a network payload, decide and document: - whether block IDs are stable across saved sessions; - whether formatting, hier","content":"Introduce context for a real service The current application does not publish editor or artifact context to the feed. Before introducing a network payload, decide and document: - whether block IDs are stable across saved sessions; - whether formatting, hierarchy, current selection, title, and metadata are required;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#extend-persistence","title":"Extend persistence","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The desktop runtime separates SQLite document/suggestion data, managed Markdown files, Pi-native configuration, project session JSONL, and launch-scoped activity. Preserve those ownership boundaries rather than replacing","content":"Extend persistence The desktop runtime separates SQLite document/suggestion data, managed Markdown files, Pi-native configuration, project session JSONL, and launch-scoped activity. Preserve those ownership boundaries rather than replacing them with one opaque React-state blob."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#document-data","title":"Document data","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Document saves contain BlockNote's serializable model and blocksToMarkdownLossy() output. Storage atomically refreshes draft.md before publishing the committed revision. Preserve that ordering and startup repair path. Te","content":"Document data Document saves contain BlockNote's serializable model and blocksToMarkdownLossy() output. Storage atomically refreshes draft.md before publishing the committed revision. Preserve that ordering and startup repair path. Temporary suggestionPreview blocks are excluded from the saved accepted document. If preview recovery is added later, store it as a separate draft concept."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#suggestion-data","title":"Suggestion data","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The live inbox, pins, workspace cards, dedupe keys, and geometry are stored as a document-scoped projection. Changes to dedupe retention should be made deliberately because a dismissed item currently cannot be re-added w","content":"Suggestion data The live inbox, pins, workspace cards, dedupe keys, and geometry are stored as a document-scoped projection. Changes to dedupe retention should be made deliberately because a dismissed item currently cannot be re-added with the same key. suggestions/state.ts is the shared renderer/storage policy boundary. Change the persisted entry types, empty-state defaults, queue limit, or eviction rules there so both processes remain consistent. Do not move persistence ownership into React as part of an unrelated feature."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#workspace-preferences","title":"Workspace preferences","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Column widths remain renderer-local preferences. Workspace-card geometry is stored per document and restored through the same clamp path because available canvas dimensions change. Add new durable data through the storag","content":"Workspace preferences Column widths remain renderer-local preferences. Workspace-card geometry is stored per document and restored through the same clamp path because available canvas dimensions change. Add new durable data through the storage-process RPC boundary. Hydrate owners at application startup and keep serialization out of display components."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#add-a-suggestion-kind","title":"Add a suggestion kind","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Adding a kind affects the discriminated union and every exhaustive presentation or behavior decision. 1. Add the literal to SUGGESTION KINDS and a new union member in types.ts. 2. Add it to the relevant canonical kind-fa","content":"Add a suggestion kind Adding a kind affects the discriminated union and every exhaustive presentation or behavior decision. 1. Add the literal to SUGGESTION KINDS and a new union member in types.ts. 2. Add it to the relevant canonical kind-family constant and guard when it is text-insertable or structural."},{"page":"extension-guide.html#add-a-custom-editor-block","title":"Add a custom editor block","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Register the block in writingSchema, then address all serialization boundaries: - accepted-document plain-text extraction; - external HTML behavior; - save/load schema compatibility; - focus and selection behavior; - age","content":"Add a custom editor block Register the block in writingSchema, then address all serialization boundaries: - accepted-document plain-text extraction; - external HTML behavior; - save/load schema compatibility; - focus and selection behavior; - agent-context inclusion or exclusion;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#implement-navigation-and-document-actions","title":"Implement navigation and document actions","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The following are static today: - New Document; - Library, Recent, Templates, Collections, Settings, Help, Archive; - Drafts, Review, Published; - history, export, share, and overflow actions. Before wiring buttons indiv","content":"Implement navigation and document actions The following are static today: - New Document; - Library, Recent, Templates, Collections, Settings, Help, Archive; - Drafts, Review, Published; - history, export, share, and overflow actions. Before wiring buttons individually, introduce the missing domain/state boundary:"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#extend-artifact-upload-or-source-retrieval","title":"Extend artifact upload or source retrieval","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The sidebar imports complete UTF-8 Markdown files through the main/storage boundary and shows persisted sources. That owner should distinguish: - upload state and errors; - stable artifact identity; - display metadata; -","content":"Extend artifact upload or source retrieval The sidebar imports complete UTF-8 Markdown files through the main/storage boundary and shows persisted sources. That owner should distinguish: - upload state and errors; - stable artifact identity; - display metadata; - UTF-8 validation state;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#evolve-the-inbox-reducer-safely","title":"Evolve the inbox reducer safely","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Use a new reducer action for a new user intent. Avoid mutating arrays in components or exposing raw dispatch outside the hook. For every transition, consider: - live, pinned, and workspace copies; - selected detail; - ac","content":"Evolve the inbox reducer safely Use a new reducer action for a new user intent. Avoid mutating arrays in components or exposing raw dispatch outside the hook. For every transition, consider: - live, pinned, and workspace copies; - selected detail; - active preview; - viewed/unread counts;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#validate-external-suggestion-data","title":"Validate external suggestion data","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"TypeScript types do not validate network input. A production feed should parse runtime payloads before emitting them. Validation should cover: - known event and suggestion kinds; - non-empty identity/dedupe fields; - tim","content":"Validate external suggestion data TypeScript types do not validate network input. A production feed should parse runtime payloads before emitting them. Validation should cover: - known event and suggestion kinds; - non-empty identity/dedupe fields; - timestamps and source-label arrays;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#introduce-routing-or-server-rendering","title":"Introduce routing or server rendering","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The current code reads browser globals during state initialization and event handling. Server rendering would require guards or client-only boundaries for: - window.localStorage and window.matchMedia in App; - document q","content":"Introduce routing or server rendering The current code reads browser globals during state initialization and event handling. Server rendering would require guards or client-only boundaries for: - window.localStorage and window.matchMedia in App; - document queries and animation frames;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#performance-watch-points","title":"Performance watch points","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"The current data volume is intentionally small. Revisit these choices as it grows: - suggestion deep copy uses JSON serialization; - workspace geometry commits update the whole reducer state; - large Mermaid diagrams ren","content":"Performance watch points The current data volume is intentionally small. Revisit these choices as it grows: - suggestion deep copy uses JSON serialization; - workspace geometry commits update the whole reducer state; - large Mermaid diagrams render client-side and inject full SVG;"},{"page":"extension-guide.html#documentation-update-triggers","title":"Documentation update triggers","section":"Extension guide","excerpt":"Update this section when a change affects any of the following: - setup, Node support, scripts, or environment variables; - service or data contracts; - state ownership or persistence; - suggestion lifecycle invariants; ","content":"Documentation update triggers Update this section when a change affects any of the following: - setup, Node support, scripts, or environment variables; - service or data contracts; - state ownership or persistence; - suggestion lifecycle invariants; - editor schema and preview rules;"}];
